"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn library's set_context and set_style functions modify the matplotlib rcParams. However, these modifications should be done before creating the figure. In this code, the figure is created after the modifications, but the scatterplot function is called without specifying the axes, which may lead to unexpected behavior if multiple figures are created. Furthermore, the rc parameter in set_context and set_style should be used with caution as it overrides existing settings.\",\n  \"patch\": \"16c16\\n<fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1)\\n---\\n>sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n>sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n>fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1)\\n18c18\\n<sns.scatterplot(x=x, y=np.sin(x + .5) * 2)\\n---\\n>sns.scatterplot(x=x, y=np.sin(x + .5) * 2, ax=ax)\"\n}"